unpackObjects

public void unpackObjects()
Description copied from class: VARDefaultTxMessage
Unpack objects
Unpack the objects in this message. The opposite of packObjects(), it restores the objects stored in this message into a usable form. The objects revived from their serialized form are stored in a Hashtable keyed by the object IDs. This methods does not return the objects. Instead, the method getObjects() is used to retrive objects belonging to specific channels.

Specified by:
unpackObjects in class VARTxMessage
See Also:
com.versant.var.message
